        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  To define MissingFileError — raised when no file is provided in the POST request body. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Missing file error signalling for API handlers. \par \b Input\/ \:  Error context (msg, filename, version). \par \b Output\/ \:  MissingFileError with default HTTP 400 Bad Request code. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(9): <ref refid="classdedoc_1_1common_1_1exceptions_1_1dedoc__error_1_1DedocError" kindref="compound">dedoc.common.exceptions.dedoc_error.DedocError</ref>] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Uses default code=400 (missing file is a client error).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Inherits full DedocError API (msg_api, filename, version, metadata). \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why no explicit code override? A: DedocError defaults to code=400 — client failed to attach a file, a Bad Request scenario. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 — Semantic template markup and LDD logging added.] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 8[Exception for missing file in request] =&gt; MissingFileError \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[MissingFileError]: APIHandler → ValidateFileAttached → NoFileFound → RaiseMissingFileError → APIResponds400 </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
